# Syra SDK integration

When writing code that calls the Syra API via `@syra-ai/sdk`:

## Response envelope

Always type and check API results as `SyraApiResponse<T>`:

```typescript
type SyraApiResponse<T = unknown> = {
  success: boolean;
  data?: T;
  error?: string;
};
```

Never trust raw `fetch` responses. Always check `result.success` before using `result.data`.

## Client factories

- **Production with auto-pay:** `createSyraPaidClient({ baseUrl: "https://api.syraa.fun" })` — reads payer from env.
- **Custom signer:** `createSyraClient({ signer })` — implement `SyraPaymentSigner.signPayment()`.
- Default base URL: `https://api.syraa.fun` (no trailing slash).

## Five pillars

Syra organizes capabilities around **Earn**, **Treasury**, **Invest**, **Spend**, and **Grow**:

```typescript
const syra = await createSyraPaidClient();
const pillars = await syra.get("/pillars");
await syra.pillars.earn.summary();
await syra.pillars.invest.opportunities();
```

Discover live routes at runtime via `GET /pillars` — do not hardcode undocumented paths.

## Route discovery

Use typed constants from the SDK:

- `SYRA_HIGH_VALUE_ROUTES` — curated high-value routes (sentiment, signal, brain, etc.)
- `SYRA_X402_ROUTE_PREFIXES` — x402-paid path prefixes
- `isSyraX402Path(pathname)` — check if a path requires payment

## Error handling

```typescript
const result = await syra.get("/news", { ticker: "BTC" });
if (!result.success) {
  // Log result.error; surface to user; do not proceed with partial data
  throw new Error(result.error ?? "Syra API call failed");
}
```

## Security

- Never hardcode keypairs or API secrets in source code.
- Use env vars: `SYRA_PAYER_KEYPAIR`, `SYRA_EVM_PAYER_PRIVATE_KEY`, `SYRA_MCP_API_KEY`.
- Validate and sanitize all user-supplied params before passing to Syra routes.

